#-Function--post_slug
  Function: post_slug
      Desc: produce a url-friendly slug string
          : string is lowercased, and non-ascii letters replaced with ascii-equivalent
          : all non-alnum characters are replaced with string {replstr} (default '_')
          : multiple occurances of {replstr} are reduced to one, and
          : leading and trailing {replstr} chars removed.
  Synopsis: {newstr}=$(post_slug {str} [{replstr}])
          : {replstr} is optional, defaults to _
   Example: post_slug '\nA title, with  sTrange  cHaracters like *&#^"@:'
          : returns "a-title-with-strange-characters-like"
          : post_slug ' A title, with  sTrange  cHaracters like *&#^@: Å Æ Ç È É Ê Ë "
          : a_title_with_strange_characters_like_a_ae_c_e_e_e_e
#-Function--post_slug---------------------------------------------------------
